To install on Ubuntu, do the following:

sudo apt-get install libtry-tiny-perl perl-tk libgtk2-imageview-perl libdevice-serialport-perl libfile-homedir-perl libfile-slurp-perl
sudo cpanp i Tk::Help Ham::Locator Ham::Resources::Utils

If your system upgrades perl, you will need to run the cpanp line again.

Allow your user ID to access the serial port
sudo usermod -a -G dialout $USER

Download rotator-control to a directory of your choosing and run
`chmod 555 rotator-control-dcu-1` to make it executable.
